Richard Hammond and James May are currently out of contract with the BBC . 
  BBC website previously featured image of trio alongside The Stig at the top of the page . 
  But now the racing driver appears solo in his white helmet . 
  BBC say the change is to reflect that none of the presenters are currently in contract . 
  Jeremy Clarkson was sacked from Top Gear after he punched producer Oisin Tymon . 
  Hammond and May also reveal they are selling off a dozen bikes from the classic motor cycle collections . 
 